properties.Summary:

properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Wind chill values are expected to moderate today before falling into the minus 45 to minus 50 range tonight into Wednesday morning. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Watch for cold related symptoms: shortness of breath, chest pain, muscle pain and weakness, numbness and colour change in fingers and toes. Extreme cold warnings are issued when very cold temperatures or wind chill creates an elevated risk to health such as frost bite and hypothermia. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to SKstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #SKStorm.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. A low pressure system over northern Hudson Bay is producing strong northwest winds gusting to 80 km/h along the Hudson Bay coast and interior portions of Kivalliq. These strong winds are producing ground blizzard conditions with visibilities near zero at times in blowing snow. Gradual improvement is expected over northern regions this afternoon and over southern regions tonight as winds slowly diminish from north to south. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Blowing Snow Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Poor visibility in snow and blowing snow is expected or occurring in some locations. Total snowfall: 10 to 20 cm today through Wednesday afternoon. Maximum wind gusts: 80 to 110 km/h. Locations: Nain to Makkovik Time span: Wednesday morning until Wednesday evening. Remarks: Fresh snowfall will combine with strengthening westerly winds Wednesday morning to produce poor visibility in blowing snow. Conditions should improve Wednesday evening. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility in some locations. Visibility may be significantly and suddenly reduced to near zero. Blowing snow advisories are issued when winds are expected to create blowing snow giving poor visibility to 800 metres or less for at least 3 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Long-lasting blizzard conditions with potentially damaging winds and persistent visibility near zero in blowing snow are expected or occurring. A strong arctic ridge of high pressure is in place over the Northwest Territories. With low pressure over Alaska, strong winds with blowing snow are expected for northern sections of the Dempster. Near the Richardson Mountains winds will increase to 90 km/h gusting to 120 this morning resulting in blizzard conditions. Blizzard conditions are forecast to last through Wednesday. ### Travel is expected to be extremely hazardous due to reduced visibility. Road closures are likely. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather in British Columbia or Yukon, send an email to BCstorm@canada.ca or YTstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #BCStorm or #YTStorm.
